Java Microservices with SpringBoot
----------------------------------
Duration: 30 days (+/- 5/10 days)
Timings: 7:10 am ist - 8:05/:10 am ist	[Monday - Friday]
         8:00 am ist - 9:00 am [Saturday/Sunday]
Fee: 4k
Notes: Live classroom notes will be shared with students on weekly basis
No recordings, no youtube, no videos will be provided. if we found any of the students recording the session, we will suspend/cancel the admission immediately without any fee refund.

pre-requisite
-------------
1. core java
2. servlet/jsp programming
3. spring framework
   1. core
	 2. aop
	 3. jdbc (optional)
	 4. transactions
	 5. datajpa
	 6. mvc
4. spring boot
5. restful services (one of them: jersey, resteasy or springrest, basic knowledge on Rest)
6. hibernate/jpa (optional)	
	
Course Content/Syllabus
------------------------
1. Concepts of Monolithic application architecture
2. Concepts of Microservices application architecture
3. Microservices Patterns
   1. API Composer (theoritical)
	 2. Command-Query Responsibility Segregation (CQRS) (theoritically)
	 3. Domain-Driven design
	 4. Database-per service
	 5. Saga (practical)
	 		1. Choreography-based saga
			2. Orchestrator-based saga
4. Implementation of microservices using tools
	1. Architecture in developing/deploying/delivering the microservices
		1.1 on Java stack
		1.2 on Devops
	2. Eureka Server (Discovery Server)
	3. Ribbon (Client-Side Loadbalancer)
	4. Spring Cloud loadbalancer
	5. Fegin
	6. Spring Circuit breaker (Resielience4J)
	7. Spring Cloud Gateway

5. Spring Cloud
	1. Spring Cloud ConfigServer
	2. Spring Cloud ConfigClient

6. Spring Security
	1. implementing WebApplication security using spring security module
	2. oauth2 security using spring security
	
7. Kafka (5 more days)
